The paper focuses on simulating the coexistence of LTE and Wi-Fi in unlicensed spectrum, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the implementation of Listen Before Talk (LBT) techniques for fair coexistence, which could be considered a security and privacy (cs.CR) issue. The use of TCP for file transfers is also mentioned, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the need for further study of implementation issues and fuller system models, which could be considered a systems and control (cs.SY) topic.
